INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('28fde7a2-c4fc-81c3-94b2-daad9c9f63b2','Cilantro Lime Butterflied Chicken Drumsticks','ğŸ”',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,1760729616541,1760729616541,0,replace('\n### **Marinade**\n\n- 1 bunch of cilantro\n- 7 garlic of cloves\n- 1 tsp black pepper\n- 2 tsp paprika powder\n- Â½ cup avocado oil (sub olive oil)\n- juice of 3 limes\n\n### **Instructions**\n\n- Start off by making the marinade. In a food processor, throw in all the ingredients for the marinade and blend until smooth. Then, set it aside.\n- Butterfly the drumsticks open. Lay them flat on a cutting board and run your knife along the thickest part, slicing until the bone is exposed. (You want to just open them up.\n- Once you do this to all of them, season them with salt and then place in a bowl. Set aside and preheat your grill to 350 degrees.\n- Cook the chicken about 3 minutes per side until you get a nice char. They will look a bit funny with no marinade. Once they are nicely charred and not burnt, baste with that marinade on one side. Then, flip them after 3 min and baste the other side.\n- Remove the chicken once it reaches an internal temperature of 175 degrees. Let cool for 3 min before serving.\n','\n',char(10)),'["1 bunch of cilantro","7 garlic cloves","1 tsp black pepper","2 tsp paprika powder","Â½ cup avocado oil (sub olive oil)","juice of 3 limes","salt"]',NULL,NULL,NULL,'team_default','public');
