INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('28fde7a2-c4fc-810a-b3ae-ccce15a656cf','Pie crust','ğŸ¥§',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,1760729616542,1760729616542,0,replace('\n## Ingredients\n\n- 1 cup cassava flour\n- 3 tablespoons arrowroot powder\n- Â¼ to Â½ teaspoon salt\n- Â½ cup palm shortening or Ghee (393)\n- 1 egg\n- 3 to 4 tablespoons cold water\n\n## Directions \n\n\nIn a food processor, add the cassava flour, arrowroot powder, and salt. Pulse to combine. Add the palm shortening or ghee and pulse until incorporated and the mixture looks like coarse crumbs. Add the egg and pulse until combined. Add the water a tablespoon at a time until the dough starts to come together and is not too sticky. Dust your hands with cassava flour and form the dough into a ball.\nPlace it on a flat, floured surface or a piece of parchment paper. Dust the dough with more cassava flour, flatten the dough into a disc, and place another piece of parchment paper on top. Roll the dough into a circle about Â¼-inch thick. Transfer the dough to a pie plate, press it into place, and crimp the edges. Poke the bottom a few times with a fork. Fill and bake the crust as indicated in the pie recipe. To pre-bake the crust for use in recipes that do not require further baking, bake in a 350 degree oven for 10 to 12 minutes, or until golden brown.\nMake it Ahead: If you are not using the dough right away, it can be wrapped in plastic wrap and stored in the refrigerator for a few days.\n\n','\n',char(10)),'["1 cup cassava flour","3 tablespoons arrowroot powder","Â¼ to Â½ teaspoon salt","Â½ cup palm shortening or Ghee (393)","1 egg","3 to 4 tablespoons cold water"]',NULL,NULL,NULL,'team_default','public');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('28fde7a2-c4fc-8193-8694-c18a8025d558','Jerk chicken wings and burnt broccoli','ğŸ”',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,1760729616542,1760729616542,0,replace('- 3 heads broccoli, cut into small florets (about 8 cups)\n- 2 tablespoons avocado oil\n- Â¾ teaspoon freshly squeezed Lemon juice\n- 2Â½ teaspoons Burnt Broccoli Seasoning (page 31)\n- 1 tablespoon ghee or extra-virgin olive oil\n- 3 pounds split chicken wings (drumettes and wingettes)\n- 3 tablespoons Caribbean Seasoning (page 33)\n\nBurnt Broccoli Seasoning\n\n- 3 tbsp fine sea salt\n- 2 tbsp garlic powder\n- 1 tbsp chili powder\n- 1 tbsp ground cumin\n- 1 tbsp onion powder\n- 1 1/2 tsp ground cinnamon\n- 1 1/2 tsp ground coriander\n- 1 1/2 tsp ground black pepper\n\nCaribbean Seasoning\n\n- 4 tsp smoked paprika\n- 4 tsp onion powder\n- 2 tsp ground allspice\n- 2 tsp sea salt\n- 2 tsp chili pwder\n- 2 tsp dried thyme\n- 1 tsp ground cinnamon\n- 1/2 tsp white pepper\n- 1/2 ground ginger\n- 1/2 cayenne pepper\n','\n',char(10)),'["3 heads broccoli, cut into small florets (about 8 cups)","2 tablespoons avocado oil","Â¾ teaspoon freshly squeezed Lemon juice","2Â½ teaspoons Burnt Broccoli Seasoning","1 tablespoon ghee or extra-virgin olive oil","3 pounds split chicken wings (drumettes and wingettes)","3 tablespoons Caribbean Seasoning","3 tbsp fine sea salt","2 tbsp garlic powder","1 tbsp chili powder","1 tbsp ground cumin","1 tbsp onion powder","1 1/2 tsp ground cinnamon","1 1/2 tsp ground coriander","1 1/2 tsp ground black pepper","4 tsp smoked paprika","4 tsp onion powder","2 tsp ground allspice","2 tsp sea salt","2 tsp chili powder","2 tsp dried thyme","1 tsp ground cinnamon","1/2 tsp white pepper","1/2 tsp ground ginger","1/2 tsp cayenne pepper"]',NULL,NULL,NULL,'team_default','public');
INSERT INTO recipes VALUES('28fde7a2-c4fc-8183-8828-deca6ea1f2b8','Middle Eastern Chicken & Rice Bowl','ğŸ”',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,1760729616542,1760729616542,0,replace('\nIngredients: \n\n- 2 lbs. chicken thighs\n- 1.5 tbsp. EVOO\n- 1 tbsp. smoked paprika\n- 1 tbsp. garlic powder\n- 1 tbsp. thyme\n- 1/2 tbsp chili flakes\n- 1/2 tsp cumin\n- 1/4 tsp. cinnamon\n- salt & pepper\n- 2 tbsp. yogurt + 1/4 cup for dressing\n- Juice of 2 lemons (1 for chicken + 1 for salad)\n- 1 red onion\n- handful cherry tomatoes\n- parsley\n- 2 tbsp. sumac (sub. lemon zest, lemon pepper, lemon juice, or vinegar)\n- 1/4 cup pickle juice\n- 2 dill pickles\n- Rice\n\n1.Add 2 lbs chicken thighs to a bowl. Drizzle with 1.5 tbsp EVOO and season with 1 tbsp smoked paprika, 1 tbsp garlic powder, 1 tbsb thyme, 1/2 tbsp chili flakes, 1/2 tsp cumin, 1/4 tsp cinnamon, a few pinches salt & ground pepper, 2 tbsp plain yogurt, & juice of 1 lemon. Mix well, then ideally let this marinate for 4-6hrs, but if you want to make it right away go ahead.\n\n\n.\n\n\n2.When youâ€™re ready to eat, bring a pan to medium heat, add 1 tbsp oil, add the chicken (brought up to room temp before cooking), and cook it through on medium heat. I used a cast iron pan and cooked on each side for 4 mins, then cooked on each side for about 1-2 minutes again. This takes about 10-12 mins depending on thickness.\n\n\n.\n\n\n3.Make the salad by thinly slicing a large red onion, a small handful of cherry tomatoes, a large handful of fresh flat parsley. Add to a bowl, sprinkle with 2-3 pinches salt, 2 tbsp of sumac, & juice of 1 large lemon. Mix well, then let it sit for about 10 mins, stirring it a couple of times.\n\n\n.\n\n\n4. Make the white sauce by mixing 1/4 cup plain yogurt, 3 tbsp mayo, 1/8 to 1/4 cup pickle juice, 2 tbsp fresh dill, a small pinch salt, & lots of fresh cracked pepper. Mix well, taste, & adjust.\n\n\n.\n\n\n5.Finally, get your base ready. To keep this lowcarb, I used my Kaizen lowcarb rice (just 6 net carbs + 20g protein per serving), but you can use regular rice too!\n\n\n.\n\n\n6.When rice is cooked, add a serving to the bowl, some chicken, then pile it high with the salad, some sliced Persian cucumbers, fresh herbs, and drizzle it up with the white sauce.\n\n','\n',char(10)),'["2 lbs chicken thighs","1.5 tbsp EVOO","1 tbsp smoked paprika","1 tbsp garlic powder","1 tbsp thyme","1/2 tbsp chili flakes","1/2 tsp cumin","1/4 tsp cinnamon","salt & pepper","2 tbsp yogurt","1/4 cup yogurt for dressing","juice of 2 lemons (1 for chicken, 1 for salad)","1 red onion","handful cherry tomatoes","parsley","2 tbsp sumac","1/4 cup pickle juice","2 dill pickles","3 tbsp mayo","2 tbsp fresh dill","rice"]',NULL,NULL,NULL,'team_default','public');
